<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-28T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-28T12:00:00-05:00" n="632" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.404/1862: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-28T12:00:00-05:00">March 28,
                                1936—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>56. Report briefly and promptly by telegraph and in detail by airmail all
                            developments tending to indicate relaxation in religious situation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>